    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I'm looking over this NDA for a new client and I'm a bit stuck on the indemnification part. Can you explain what this actually means for me personally? Here is the text:\n\n\"The Recipient shall indemnify, defend, and hold harmless the Disclosing Party from and against any and all losses, damages, liabilities, deficiencies, claims, actions, judgments, settlements, interest, awards, penalties, fines, costs, or expenses of whatever kind, including reasonable attorneys' fees, arising out of or occurring in connection with any breach of this Agreement or the negligence or willful misconduct of the Recipient or its representatives.\"",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Indemnification refers to the obligation of the Recipient to reimburse the Disclosing Party for any losses, damages, or related costs that may arise due to breaches, negligence, or misconduct by the Recipient or their representatives. In this clause, the Recipient assumes financial responsibility for any negative consequences linked to the agreement and its actions. This means you might be personally liable for covering their legal expenses and compensating them for any claims, judgments, or other expenses that might occur due to your attempts to breach the terms or through accidental or intentional improper actions by you or your representatives. It's important to carefully review this necessity and understand your potential exposure under this agreement.",
