      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. i guess i'm just worried about these things being \"sneaky\" or catching me out when i'm not looking. are there any specific red flags or things that feel particularly predatory or \"sneaky\" in these kinds of contracts that i should be on the lookout for?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Absolutely, vigilance is key, and there are several red flags you should watch for. First, broad and all-encompassing indemnification clauses without specific limitations can be overreaching. Similarly, indemnification for the 'bad faith' or 'intentional and willful misconduct' of the indemnifying party is uncommon and a potential trap. Also, check for any clause that requires you to indemnify not just for your actions, but also for the actions of connected parties you can't fully control, such as third parties. Furthermore, vague terms or those with undefined scopes can create ambiguity, leading to excessive liability. Pay attention to these areas, and always negotiate clauses that are too broad or unfair, or better yet, have an experienced attorney examine them for you before you sign.",
